Description: Fragment of amygdaloid handle from a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium brown; grey core; some mica. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Type series: KT1245 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Name Philippos. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 201, 44
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0297)
